Your ` strConn = strConn` strings are not concatenated properly.

Your variables aren&#39;t evaluating, their names are just being put straight into the string.

Change, e.g.

     strConn = strConn &amp; &quot;Initial Catalog= &amp; pCatalog; &amp; Data Source= &amp; pServer;&quot;
     strConn = strConn &amp; &quot;Integrated Security=sspi;&amp; UserID= &amp; pUser; &amp; Password= &amp; pPsw;&quot;


to

     strConn = strConn &amp; &quot;Initial Catalog=&quot; &amp; pCatalog &amp; &quot;;Data Source=&quot; &amp; pServer &amp; &quot;;&quot;
     strConn = strConn &amp; &quot;Integrated Security=sspi;User ID= &quot;&amp; pUser; &amp; &quot;Password= &quot; &amp; pPsw &amp; &quot;;&quot;

In addition to the issue of an unrecognised token you have another issue that you would encounter. The issues are :-

- a) You delete from a TABLE **not the database**, which may (WILL) have multiple tables. 

- b) you need to enclose a String in single quotes, that is use uuid=&#39;d21a141d-7ac5-487b-a5af-6eae0825ac37&#39;. You could change ......` + &quot;=&quot; + c.getId()` to ......` + &quot;=&#39;&quot; + c.getId() + &quot;&#39;&quot;`. 

However, it is recommended that values are bound (typically you use a **`?`** place-holder which is replaced with the value, it being suitably enclosed (e.g. the single quotes added)), thus protecting against SQL injection.

A complete fix would be to change :-

    public void deleteCheckIn(CheckIn c) {
        mDataBase.delete(DATABASE_NAME,  CheckInTable.Cols.UUID + &quot;=&quot; + c.getId(), null);
    }

to 

    public int deleteCheckIn(CheckIn c) {
        return mDataBase.delete(CheckInTable.NAME,  CheckInTable.Cols.UUID + &quot;=?&quot;, new String[]{c.getId()});
    }

The above will :-

- Use the table instead of the database, eliminating the table not found exception that was about to happen.
- correct the unrecognised token.
- protect against SQL injection.
- return the number of rows that were deleted, which may be useful to know (e.g. if 0 no rows were deleted).

